The paper discusses the effectiveness of ultrasonic transmissions in disrupting nearby microphones, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the practical implementation of a wearable bracelet as a jammer, which involves hardware design and engineering (cs.SY). The evaluation of the jammer under practical scenarios involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with disrupting audio recordings. Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations and areas for improvement, which could fall under the category of software development (cs.SD).
